{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17524378","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17524378"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:03:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:03:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13986"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13986"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.8,0.08,0,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6620"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55100"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6620","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6620"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13986"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"40618"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"247"},{"type":"tags","id":"377"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8235"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"13428"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13429"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44559"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44801"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45080"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/55100"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 85-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-month history of a painless lump in her right breast. She has a medical history of hypertension, osteoarthritis, and type 2 diabetes. Her regular medications include metformin, amlodipine, and paracetamol. On examination, she appears well. Her pulse rate is 72/min, blood pressure 138/82 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. At the start of the physical examination of the breast the patient is asked to lift her arms (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the pertinent physical finding shown?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Protruding breast mass","Skin tethering","Paget\u0027s disease of the nipple","Nodular melanoma","Peau d\u0027orange"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe image shows \u003Cstrong\u003Eskin tethering\u003C/strong\u003E, which is a characteristic sign of locally advanced breast cancer. Skin tethering occurs when the tumor involves Cooper\u0027s ligaments, causing the skin to be pulled inward, creating a dimpled or puckered appearance. This finding is significant as it suggests that the cancer has progressed beyond the early stages and may be involving surrounding tissues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Eprotruding breast mass\u003C/strong\u003E would appear as an outward bulging or protrusion of the breast tissue, which is not evident in this image. While a protruding mass can be a sign of breast cancer, it is not the specific finding shown here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPeau d\u0027orange\u003C/strong\u003E refers to a skin appearance resembling an orange peel, caused by lymphatic obstruction in inflammatory breast cancer. This would present as a diffuse thickening and pitting of the skin, which is not seen in this image.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPaget\u0027s disease of the nipple\u003C/strong\u003E is a rare form of breast cancer that affects the nipple and areola. It typically presents as a scaly, red, or crusted appearance of the nipple and surrounding area, which is not visible in this image.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENodular melanoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a type of skin cancer that typically appears as a raised, firm, and often darkly pigmented lesion. While it can occur on the breast, it is not the finding shown in this image, which demonstrates skin tethering rather than a distinct nodular lesion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe presence of skin tethering in this elderly patient with a two-month history of a breast lump is concerning for malignancy. It\u0027s important to note that older patients may present with more advanced disease due to delayed presentation or reduced breast awareness. This patient requires prompt referral for further investigation, including imaging (mammography and ultrasound) and tissue sampling (core needle biopsy) to confirm the diagnosis and stage the disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Skin tethering is a sign of locally advanced breast cancer, indicating possible involvement of Cooper\u0027s ligaments.","Physical examination findings such as skin changes are crucial in the assessment of breast masses.","Breast cancer in elderly patients may present with more advanced disease due to delayed presentation."],"references":["Naraynsingh V, Jarvis JK, Milne DM, Cawich SO, Harnanan D, Singh Y, Islam S. The Pushing Sign for Early Skin Tethering in Breast Cancer. Cureus. 2021 Dec 16;13(12):e20471. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8682950/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"40618"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13986"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20881"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20881","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20881"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/wuUUj0YHWwjFLFxgbg0v8iJm3dGls3.jpg","thumbUrl":"htt